The paper discusses requirements engineering and software engineering practices, which are typically covered under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The use of UML and VHDL_AMS suggests a focus on system design and development, which falls under the cs.SD (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also discusses practical problems in introducing new requirements engineering methods, which could be classified under the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The use of the Uplink Framework for wireless mobile phone applications suggests a focus on the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the verification of the uplink path, which could be classified under the cs.ET (Embedded Systems) sub-category.
